sentences: He adopted the name "Le Castle Vania" with the release of his remix for Snowden's song "Black Eyes" in 2006.
From 2007 to 2012, Le Castle Vania hosted the "Fuck Yesss" indie electronica dance parties at venues such as The Drunken Unicorn and Masquerade in Atlanta.
In 2008, URB Magazine included Le Castle Vania in their list of "Next 100" artists to watch.
In 2014, Eiland contributed to the soundtrack of the film John Wick with 4 original songs.

On October 21, 2015, Eiland contributed three new songs to the video game Payday 2 as a part of the game's yearly anniversary event, Crimefest, and later contributed two more songs in October 2018 as part of that year's Crimefest, dubbed "Breaking News."
